!! Help page fields

|!Field |!Required |!Type |!Description |
|`llm-help-path` |yes |string |Space-separated list of paths. Each path is `/`-delimited (e.g., `data-model/person/create`). |
|`llm-help-description` |yes |string |One-line summary shown when this page appears in a parent's subtopic listing. |
|`llm-help-sort` |no |string |Numeric sort key for ordering among siblings. Pages without sort are ordered alphabetically by path segment. |
|`llm-help-context` |no |string |Space-separated context keys. If set, page is only visible when active context intersects. If absent, page is always visible. |

!! Tag

All help pages must be tagged: `$:/tags/rimir/llm-help/page`

!! Tool schema

```json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "path": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Help path. Empty for root."
    },
    "context": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Optional context override (space-separated keys)."
    }
  }
}
```

!! Filter functions (`$:/plugins/rimir/llm-help/functions`)

|!Function |!Parameters |!Returns |
|`_llm-help-all-pages` |none |All help page tiddler titles |
|`_llm-help-ctx-pages` |`ctx` |Pages with `llm-help-context` matching ctx |
|`_llm-help-visible-pages` |`ctx` |Pages visible in given context (context-free + context-matched) |
|`_llm-help-resolve-ctx` |`ctx` |Effective context (param or state tiddler) |
|`_llm-help-root-page` |`ctx` |Root page tiddler (blank path) |
|`_llm-help-at` |`path, ctx` |Page tiddler at exact path |
|`_llm-help-all-paths` |`ctx` |All individual paths from visible pages |
|`_llm-help-child-segments` |`prefix, ctx` |Unique next-level path segments |

!! State tiddlers

|!Tiddler |!Purpose |
|`$:/temp/rimir/llm-help/active-context` |Active context keys (space-separated). Transient — resets on reload. Set by the environment (e.g., appify sets it when an app becomes active). |

!! User shortcut tiddlers

User-created shortcuts live at `$:/llm-help/user/<slug>` and are tagged `$:/tags/rimir/llm-help/page` with `llm-help-path: shortcuts/<slug>`.

